text: Ahmed Mohamed Shafik Zaki (; born 25 November 1941) is an Egyptian politician. He is a former candidate for the presidency of Egypt. He was a senior commander in the Egyptian Air Force and later served as Prime Minister of Egypt from 29 January 2011 to 3 March 2011. ==References== Category:1941 births Category:Living people Category:Prime Ministers of Egypt Category:Politicians from Cairo
title: Ahmed Shafik
